<article class="article">
  <h2>Why step up your SIP?</h2>
  <p>Most people start a SIP they can afford today and never revise it, even as their salary grows 8–10% a year. A step-up SIP fixes that leak: the instalment automatically rises every year, so your investment rate keeps pace with your income. Because the increases arrive early in your investing life and then compound for decades, the effect on the final corpus is far larger than the extra money you put in.</p>

  <h2>How the calculation works</h2>
  <p>The calculator simulates the SIP month by month. Each month's instalment earns the monthly return until the end of the period, and at the end of every 12 months the instalment increases by your chosen step-up percentage:</p>
  <div class="formula">Instalment in year k = P × (1 + step)<sup>k−1</sup></div>
  <p>The flat-SIP comparison line uses the same return with no step-up, so the gap you see is purely the effect of increasing your contributions.</p>

  <h2>Worked example</h2>
  <p>Start at ₹10,000 a month, step up 10% yearly, 12% p.a. return, 20 years. You invest about ₹68.7 lakh in total (versus ₹24 lakh flat), and the corpus reaches roughly <strong>₹1.85 crore</strong> versus ₹92 lakh for the flat SIP. The step-up contributed ₹44.7 lakh more of your money but produced about ₹93 lakh more corpus — the difference is compounding on the earlier, larger instalments.</p>

  <h2>How to use this calculator</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Set your starting SIP, annual step-up percentage, expected return and period.</li>
    <li>The "vs flat SIP" tile shows exactly how much extra corpus the step-up creates.</li>
    <li>Open the table to see your instalment, cumulative investment and value for each year.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
  function recalc() {
    var p0 = CM.val('p'), step = CM.val('s') / 100, rate = CM.val('r'), yrs = CM.val('n');
    var i = rate / 1200, n = Math.round(yrs * 12);
    if (p0 <= 0 || n <= 0) return;

    var bal = 0, flatBal = 0, inv = 0, p = p0;
    var labels = [], valSeries = [], flatSeries = [], rows = [];
    for (var mth = 1; mth <= n; mth++) {
      bal = (bal + p) * (1 + i);
      flatBal = (flatBal + p0) * (1 + i);
      inv += p;
      if (mth % 12 === 0 || mth === n) {
        var y = Math.ceil(mth / 12);
        labels.push('Y' + y); valSeries.push(bal); flatSeries.push(flatBal);
        rows.push([y, CM.inr(p), CM.inr(inv), CM.inr(bal)]);
        if (mth % 12 === 0) p = p * (1 + step);
      }
    }
    CM.set('out-fv', CM.inr(bal));
    var w = CM.words(bal);
    CM.set('out-fv-sub', w ? 'about ' + w : '');
    CM.set('out-inv', CM.inr(inv));
    CM.set('out-gain', CM.inr(bal - inv));
    CM.set('out-extra', '+' + CM.compact(bal - flatBal));

    CM.lineChart('chart-growth', labels, [
      { label: 'Step-up SIP', data: valSeries, role: '--s1', fill: true },
      { label: 'Flat SIP', data: flatSeries, role: '--s2' }
    ]);
    CM.table('sched-out', ['Year', 'Monthly SIP', 'Invested (cum.)', 'Value'], rows);
  }
  CM.bind(['p', 's', 'r', 'n'], recalc);
});
</script>
